Mamertine domination. The principle display cases focus on the cemeteries and religious areas of the city. The grounds of the museum contain a number of monuments and architectural pieces (many from the post-medieval city that was destroyed in the 1908 earthquake) but some earlier as well, principally Roman in date",{"settlement":85,"region":85,"country":118,"address":119,"geo":120},"Italy","Viale della Liberta 465, Messina",{"lat":121,"lon":122},38.2166927,15.5639472,{"_":124,"type":125},"A3576","inventory",{"_":127,"mainLang":128,"languages":129},"Ancient Greek","grc",[127],{"type":131,"bibl":132},"edition",[133,146],{"type":134,"n":135,"author":136,"date":137,"citedRange":138,"ptr":139,"ref":141,"inscriptionDate":137,"title":143,"citation":144,"uri":145,"year":137},"corpus","IMusMessina","Bitto","2001","19",{"target":140},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/M9HMEP2R",{"_":142,"target":142},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000029","Le iscrizioni greche e latine di Messina","\u003Cspan>Irma Bitto, \u003Ci>Le iscrizioni greche e latine di Messina\u003C/i>, vol. 1, Pelorias 7 (Messina: Dipartimento di Scienze dell’Antichità dell’Università degli Studi di Messina, 2001)\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/M9HMEP2R",{"type":147,"n":148,"author":149,"title":150,"date":151,"citedRange":152,"ptr":153,"ref":154,"inscriptionDate":155,"citation":156,"uri":157,"year":158},"bulletin","NSA","","Notizie degli scavi di antichità","1876-","82 no. 1 fig. 20",{"target":154},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV","1942","\u003Cspan>Accademia nazionale dei Lincei, Istituto nazionale di archeologia e storia dell’arte (Italy), e Reale Accademia d’Italia, «Notizie degli scavi di antichità», \u003Ci>Notizie degli Scavi di Antichità\u003C/i>, 1876, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/4MCP2PVV","1876",{"type":160,"bibl"